    <title type="html"><![CDATA[hermesJMS With hornetQ]]></title>
    <link href="http://wolfmotto.github.io/blog/2014/06/18/hermesjms-with-hornetq/"/>
    <updated>2014-06-18T17:10:09+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://wolfmotto.github.io/blog/2014/06/18/hermesjms-with-hornetq</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>The prerequisite of this post is that the hornetQ server is already configured to work with Jboss server (i.e. Jboss 7)</em></p>

<p><strong>The environment with below tools:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>HermesJMS v1.14</li>
  <li>HornetQ Server version 2.2.21.Final</li>
  <li>Jboss 7</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>1) Get <a href="http://www.hermesjms.com" title="hermesjms">HermesJMS</a> and install HermesJMS v1.14</strong></p>

<p><strong>2) New a JMS session through ‘Actions’ menu</strong></p>

<p><strong>3) Switch to ‘Providers’ tab and configure classpathgroup, name it ‘hornetq’</strong> <em>(add the jboss-client.jar, you can get this jar file from Jboss7 distribution)</em></p>

<p><img src="http://wolfmotto.github.io/images/hermesjms/02.jpg" alt="hornetq" /></p>

<p><strong>4) Configure ConnectionFactory as below</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Class  : select ‘hermes.JNDIConnectionFactory’  </li>
  <li>Loader : select ‘hornetq’ </li>
</ul>

<p><img src="http://wolfmotto.github.io/images/hermesjms/01.jpg" alt="ConnectionFactory" /></p>

<p><strong>5) Add Topic or Queue to the JMS session</strong> <em>(below with a topic=/topic/commonEntity/v1)</em></p>

<p><img src="http://wolfmotto.github.io/images/hermesjms/03.jpg" alt="ConnectionFactory" /></p>

<p><strong>6) Click the Topic or Queue to watch the incoming JMS messages</strong></p>

<p><img src="http://wolfmotto.github.io/images/hermesjms/05.jpg" alt="ConnectionFactory" /></p>

<p><em>Reference:</em></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://community.jboss.org/wiki/UsingHermesJMSWithHornetQ" title="UsingHermesJMSWithHornetQ">HermesJMSWithHornetQ on Jboss</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="http://xebee.xebia.in/index.php/2014/03/16/soap-over-jms-with/">HermesJMS and ActiveMQ integration with SoapUI</a></p>
  </li>
</ol>

